1.000000   TBD

  - BREAKING: AppHandler->client_tag now croaks on missing name or
    coordinate. Previously these were silently passed as undef into the
    tag array.
  - BREAKING: Key->new now rejects passing both privkey and pubkey
    (previously silently preferred privkey). Message->new now rejects
    AUTH with both event and challenge, and COUNT with both count and
    filters. All three cases now croak immediately.
  - BREAKING: Message REQ and COUNT constructors now validate that each
    element in the filters array is a Net::Nostr::Filter object. Previously
    non-Filter values were silently accepted and failed during serialization.
  - New: NIP-77 negentropy syncing now fully integrated into Client and
    Relay. Client gains neg_open, neg_msg, neg_close methods and neg_msg,
    neg_err callbacks. Relay handles NEG-OPEN/NEG-MSG/NEG-CLOSE messages
    and drives server-side reconciliation.
  - Fix: NIP-42 relay URL matching now supports bracketed IPv6 addresses
    (e.g. ws://[::1]:8080). Previously these failed to parse and were
    always rejected.
  - BREAKING: Callback arguments (on_success, on_failure, Client->on,
    Client->connect callback) now require CODE refs. Previously non-code
    values were silently accepted and would fail at invocation time.
  - BREAKING: Message COUNT count and NEG-ERR neg_limit fields now
    validate as non-negative integers. Previously these were silently
    coerced via Perl numeric conversion from untrusted wire data.
  - BREAKING: Identifier->parse() now rejects domains containing
    whitespace, /, :, ?, #, [], or control characters. Previously these
    were silently accepted and interpolated into fetch URLs.
  - BREAKING: Relay connections(), subscriptions(), and
    authenticated_pubkeys() now return snapshots (copies) instead of
    live internal references. Mutating the returned hashrefs no longer
    affects relay state.
  - New: Relay production hardening with configurable resource limits:
    max_subscriptions, max_filters, max_content_length, max_event_tags,
    max_limit, default_limit, created_at_lower_limit, created_at_upper_limit,
    max_message_length, and on_event policy callback. All limits are opt-in
    with sane defaults (unlimited). Names match NIP-11 limitation fields.
  - New: Relay idle_timeout option disconnects inactive clients after a
    configurable period. Timer resets on each client message.
  - New: Relay shutdown_timeout option and graceful_stop method. Sends a
    NOTICE to all clients before closing connections, giving them time to
    reconnect to another relay.
  - Performance: Filter.matches() now uses O(1) hash set lookups for ids,
    authors, and kinds instead of O(n) grep. Search terms are pre-parsed
    and lowercased at construction time. Tag matching uses hash sets.
  - Performance: RelayStore.delete_by_id now uses binary search + single
    splice instead of O(n) grep to rebuild the ordered array.
  - Performance: Relay broadcast uses an inverted subscription index by
    kind, reducing fanout from O(connections * subscriptions) to
    O(matching_subscriptions) for kind-filtered subscriptions.
  - Fix: Relay broadcast index now correctly handles mixed-filter
    subscriptions (filters with and without kinds in the same REQ).
    Previously, a subscription with both kind-filtered and kind-less
    filters would miss events matching only the kind-less filter.
  - Fix: NIP-09 a-tag deletion now works for replaceable events
    (kind 0, 3, 10000-19999) in addition to addressable events.
    Deletion::applies_to and RelayStore::delete_matching updated.
  - Fix: Client _setup_handlers now uses weakened self-reference to
    prevent circular reference memory leak when Client objects are
    dropped without calling disconnect
  - New: Net::Nostr::DVM (NIP-90) - data vending machine with job
    requests (kind 5000-5999), job results (kind 6000-6999), job
    feedback (kind 7000), encrypted params, job chaining, and
    service provider discoverability
  - New: Net::Nostr::Wiki (NIP-54) - wiki articles (kind 30818) with
    d tag normalization, merge requests (kind 818) with source markers,
    wiki redirects (kind 30819), fork/defer markers, and wikilink
    resolution for Djot content
  - New: Net::Nostr::LiveActivity (NIP-53) - live activities with live
    streaming events (kind 30311), chat messages (kind 1311), meeting
    spaces (kind 30312), meeting room events (kind 30313), and room
    presence (kind 10312) with participant roles and proof of agreement
  - New: Net::Nostr::RelayAccess (NIP-43) - relay access metadata and
    requests with membership lists (kind 13534), add/remove member
    (kinds 8000/8001), join/invite/leave requests (kinds 28934/28935/28936),
    all with NIP-70 protected tags
  - New: Net::Nostr::MintDiscovery (NIP-87) - ecash mint discoverability
    with recommendation events (kind 38000), Cashu mint info (kind 38172),
    and Fedimint info (kind 38173)
  - New: Net::Nostr::Calendar (NIP-52) - date-based (kind 31922) and
    time-based (kind 31923) calendar events, calendar collections
    (kind 31924), and RSVPs (kind 31925) with common tag infrastructure,
    deprecated name tag handling, and free/busy semantics
  - New: Net::Nostr::Torrent (NIP-35) - kind 2003 torrent index events
    with info hash, files, trackers, tag prefixes, and searchable hashtags;
    kind 2004 torrent comments following NIP-10 tagging
  - New: Net::Nostr::ExternalId (NIP-73) - external content ID tag builders
    and parser for URLs, ISBNs, geohashes, ISO 3166 codes, ISANs, DOIs,
    hashtags, podcasts, and blockchain transactions/addresses
  - New: Net::Nostr::Metadata (NIP-24) - kind 0 profile metadata with
    display_name, website, banner, bot, birthday; standard tag helpers
    for hashtags, URLs, and titles; deprecated field migration
  - New: Net::Nostr::Badge (NIP-58) - badge definitions (kind 30009),
    awards (kind 8), profile badges (kind 10008), and badge sets (kind 30008)
  - New: NIP-70 protected events — relay rejects events with ["-"] tag
    unless the author is authenticated via NIP-42; Event->is_protected
  - New: Net::Nostr::AppData (NIP-78) - kind 30078 addressable events for
    arbitrary custom app data storage (remoteStorage-like capabilities)
  - New: Net::Nostr::RelayMonitor (NIP-66) - kind 30166 relay discovery
    events and kind 10166 monitor announcement events for relay discovery
    and liveness monitoring
  - New: Net::Nostr::FileMetadata (NIP-94) - kind 1063 file metadata events
    for organizing and classifying shared files with URL, MIME type, SHA-256
    hashes, dimensions, thumbnails, fallback sources, and more
  - New: Net::Nostr::Negentropy (NIP-77) - negentropy set reconciliation
    for efficient event syncing between clients and relays
  - New: Message types NEG-OPEN, NEG-MSG, NEG-CLOSE, NEG-ERR in
    Net::Nostr::Message for NIP-77 protocol flow
  - New: Net::Nostr::RelayAdmin (NIP-86) - relay management API client
  - New: Net::Nostr::HttpAuth (NIP-98) - HTTP auth using nostr events
  - New: Net::Nostr::KeyEncrypt (NIP-49) - private key encryption with
    scrypt key derivation and XChaCha20-Poly1305 AEAD encryption
  - New: Net::Nostr::Mention (NIP-27) - extract, replace, and build
    nostr: mentions in event content
  - New: Net::Nostr::Relay::Store - indexed in-memory event storage backend
    with O(1) duplicate detection, replaceable/addressable lookups, and
    index-accelerated queries by kind, author, id, and tag
  - New: Relay now uses pluggable storage via the store constructor option.
    Third-party backends (SQLite, LMDB) can implement the same duck-typed
    interface. Default: indexed in-memory store
  - New: Relay max_events option for configurable event capacity with
    FIFO eviction of oldest events when the limit is exceeded
  - New: Relay event_rate_limit option for per-connection rate limiting
    (e.g. '10/60' for 10 events per 60 seconds)
  - New: Relay inject_event method for storing events without validation
    or broadcasting (useful for tests and programmatic seeding)
  - Relay events accessor now returns a snapshot (array copy). Mutating
    the returned arrayref no longer affects the relay's internal state
  - New: Event->from_wire strict wire parser validates all 7 NIP-01 fields
    (id, pubkey, created_at, kind, tags, content, sig) are present and
    defined. Message->parse now uses from_wire instead of Event->new, so
    malformed wire events are rejected rather than silently normalized
  - Tighten NIP-46 payload parsers: parse_request now rejects missing id,
    method, or params (and non-arrayref params); parse_response rejects
    missing id. Request and Response constructors enforce the same rules.
  - Tighten NIP-47 payload parsers: parse_info now rejects wrong event kind;
    parse_response rejects missing result_type; parse_notification rejects
    missing notification_type or notification. Constructors enforce the same.
  - BREAKING: Net::Nostr::Event is now immutable after construction. Body
    fields (id, pubkey, created_at, kind, tags, content) are read-only.
    Only sig remains writable. add_pubkey_ref and add_event_ref removed.
  - Fix: Event tags are now deep-copied on input and output to prevent
    aliasing through retained references from silently invalidating the
    event ID or signature
  - BREAKING: All constructors now reject unknown arguments. This affects
    Relay, Key, Message, Filter, Identifier, List, Client, Blossom,
    FollowList, RelayList, Nutzap, Community, AppHandler,
    ClassifiedListing, Article, Marketplace, Label, MediaAttachment,
    Wallet, and all WalletConnect/RemoteSigning inner classes.
    Callers passing typo'd or unsupported keys will now get a croak.
  - Filter: search field now rejects references (must be a plain string)
  - Harden validation across all modules: pubkeys, event IDs, signatures,
    relay URLs, and tag shapes are now strictly validated as 64-char
    lowercase hex where applicable
  - Event constructor now validates all fields (kind range, hex formats,
    tags structure, created_at)
  - Filter constructor now rejects empty arrays for list fields, validates
    kind ranges and numeric fields
  - Message constructor now validates subscription_id format, requires
    message for NOTICE and CLOSED, validates event_id as 64-char hex for
    OK, requires event to be a Net::Nostr::Event object for EVENT/AUTH,
    rejects reference values for message/challenge fields, requires
    subscription_id for EOSE/CLOSED
  - Message parser now rejects non-scalar values for string fields
    (subscription_id, message, challenge) in all message types
  - Relay now applies filter limits per-filter (not globally), improved
    error handling for malformed messages
  - Bech32 decoder now validates exact byte lengths for TLV payloads
  - WalletConnect now requires lowercase hex for secret and wallet_pubkey
  - DirectMessage now validates recipient pubkeys, reply_to, and quote IDs
  - Comment now validates pubkeys, quote IDs, and mention pubkeys
  - Channel now validates channel_id and message_id hex format
  - Improved POD documentation across all modules with code examples
  - Add NIP-11 support (Relay information document)
  - Add NIP-28 support (Public chat)
  - Add NIP-51 support (Lists)
  - Add NIP-51 git authors (10017) and git repositories (10018) lists
  - Add NIP-29 support (Relay-based groups)
  - Add NIP-59 support (Gift wrap)
  - Add NIP-17 support (Private direct messages)
  - Add NIP-65 support (Relay list metadata)
  - Add NIP-13 support (Proof of Work)
  - Add NIP-05 support (DNS-based internet identifiers)
  - Add NIP-57 support (Lightning Zaps)
  - Add NIP-22 support (Comment)
  - Add NIP-34 support (git stuff)
  - Add NIP-03 support (OpenTimestamps attestations)
  - Add NIP-40 support (Expiration timestamp)
  - Add NIP-45 support (Event counts)
  - Add NIP-25 support (Reactions)
  - Add NIP-18 support (Reposts)
  - Add NIP-06 support (Basic key derivation from mnemonic seed phrase)
  - Add NIP-47 support (Nostr Wallet Connect)
  - Add NIP-46 support (Nostr Remote Signing)
  - Add NIP-50 support (Search capability)
  - Add NIP-21 support (nostr: URI scheme)
  - Add NIP-23 support (Long-form content)
  - Add NIP-60 support (Cashu wallets)
  - Add NIP-61 support (Nutzaps)
  - Add NIP-15 support (Nostr Marketplace)
  - Add NIP-89 support (Recommended Application Handlers)
  - Add NIP-B7 support (Blossom media)
  - Add NIP-72 support (Moderated Communities)
  - Add NIP-32 support (Labeling)
  - Add NIP-36 support (Sensitive Content / Content Warning)
  - Add NIP-56 support (Reporting)
  - Add NIP-92 support (Media Attachments)
  - Add NIP-99 support (Classified Listings)

